    "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Include the v2.9.15 HTTP paths in the validation matrix**\n\nThis v2.9.15 support matrix is the artifact that tells operators which software paths still need hardware validation, but it only lists the old six-option/SVM3/session-status work and omits the newly advertised `http_handoff_http` preset, HTTP monitor, BDMV HTTP probe, and HDMI sequencing paths from this release. In the hardware-validation context, testers following this matrix would not exercise the new pure-HTTP paths even though `addon.xml` and the release notes present them as v2.9.15 runtime changes.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
